The paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of Dynamic Movement Primitives (DMPs) in robotic applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new set of basis functions, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of multiple observations, which could relate to Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
